  "text": "In Metropolis sampling Metropolis et al. [CITATION_1] ; see also Brooks 12 ; Gilks et al. 14 , q is chosen so that it is symmetric with respect to its arguments, q y | Ω t q Ω t | y . The acceptance probability then simplifies to α y | Ω t min 1, π y /π Ω t . A popular choice for q is the normal distribution centered at the current value of the chain.",
